1.00	Solonchak	Solonchak	Solonchak (Russian and Ukrainian: Солончак) is pale or grey soil type found in arid to subhumid, poorly drained conditions. The word is Russian for "salt marsh" in turn from Russian sol (соль), "salt".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Solontchak.jpg/220px-Solontchak.jpg
